## Context Commands & Protocols

### Session Management Commands
When using this context, the following commands are available:

**@session-status** - Displays current workflow progress, session metrics, and next steps
**@session-save [description]** - Manually saves current session state with description
**@session-resume [session_id]** - Resumes a previously saved workflow session
**@session-compress** - Compresses current context to reduce token usage
**@session-split [reason]** - Splits current session when approaching limits
**@session-complete [outcome]** - Marks session complete with outcome summary

### Quality Assurance Commands
**@quality-check** - Runs automated quality validation on current work
**@quality-report** - Generates quality assessment report for session
**@quality-improve [aspect]** - Provides specific improvement suggestions

### Recovery Commands
**@recovery-point [label]** - Creates a recovery point with custom label
**@recovery-restore [label]** - Restores to specified recovery point
**@recovery-list** - Lists all available recovery points

## Session Structure Protocol

### Session Initialization (First 10 minutes)
1. **Context Loading:** Load previous session state or initialize new workflow
2. **Objective Review:** Confirm current session objectives and priorities
3. **Resource Check:** Verify access to required files and tools
4. **Progress Assessment:** Review progress toward overall workflow goals

### Session Execution (Core Work Time)
1. **Task Execution:** Work on planned tasks with quality checkpoints
2. **State Preservation:** Regular state saves (every 15-20 minutes)
3. **Token Monitoring:** Watch for approaching context limits
4. **Quality Validation:** Apply quality checks at natural stopping points

### Session Completion (Final 15 minutes)
1. **Work Validation:** Ensure session objectives achieved
2. **State Preservation:** Comprehensive state save with next session plan
3. **Quality Assessment:** Generate quality report for completed work
4. **Transition Planning:** Prepare clear objectives for next session

## Context Optimization Strategies

### Token Efficiency Patterns
**Automatic Optimizations:**
- Context summarization when approaching 70% token capacity
- Progressive detail reduction for completed sections
- File-based reference replacement for detailed content
- Automatic cleanup of temporary working data

**Manual Optimization Commands:**
- `@compress-context [level]` - Apply compression with specified intensity
- `@summarize-completed` - Replace detailed completed sections with summaries
- `@archive-session-data` - Move completed work to archive files

### Memory Management
**Context Size Monitoring:**
- Real-time token usage display
- Automatic warnings at 50%, 75%, and 90% capacity
- Compression suggestions based on content type
- Session splitting recommendations

**Smart Context Loading:**
- Load only relevant context for current session phase
- Lazy loading of reference materials
- Automatic cleanup of unused context elements
- Progressive context building as work advances

